<br>
Been talkin with Magi around the globe, and most magi claim the new lvl 44 LoY spell, Primal Remedy, is rather useless.<br>
<br>
Any quest a person can solo is worth doing at least once, so I decided to buck the system (as usual) and do it anyhow.  I finally got the piece I needed to complete it last night, tho I have yet to do the actual turn-in.  So gathering what I could from our dear friend Lucy, this is what I found:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3699&amp;source=Live" target="top">Primal Remedy</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Increase Hitpoints v2 by 80 per tick <br>
Mana: 200 Skill: Alteration <br>
Casting Time: 4 Recast Time: 7.5 <br>
Fizzle Time: 2.5 Range: 100 <br>
 <br>
comparing it to the heal I have been using as my only viable pet heal...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2536&amp;source=Live" target="top">Transon's Elemental Infusion</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Increase Hitpoints by 556 (L52) to 580 (L60) <br>
Decrease Disease Counter by 10 <br>
Mana: 275 Skill: Conjuration <br>
Casting Time: 5 Recast Time: 7.5 <br>
Fizzle Time: 2.25 Range: 100 <br>
<br>
OK, some things to consider before bothering with this spell or not.  First is, is your specialization in Conjuration?  If so, then the primal remedy which is alteration won't be as mana effective as it could be.  Whereas the elemental infusion IS conjuration.<br>
<br>
I see two prime uses for this spell.<br>
<br>
1)  Obviously as a supplemental heal to run in tandem with TEI.  These two can almost create a chain-healing effect.  A single cast of each will run just under 2.2k hp recovered in a span of 6 ticks if chained.<br>
<br>
2)  To help buffer your pet to cover your ass while you run for your life!  (something I do frequently)  The idea of a lower mana alternative to dump on your pet just before you bail isn't a bad thing.  Leaving a regen'd Earth pet to hold a couple adds while you run to the zone will do wonders for your party should they be fleeing with you.  I wonder if this stacks with most clerical HoT's?  If so, you and the cleric dump your HoT on the pet and put your runnin shoes on haha.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, I would say this spell IS worth getting from the info I have thus far.  Tho for almost any mage, in a battle with your pet tanking and you are the only available healer for the pet, chances are you are better off spending that mana tryin to blast the enemy down instead of spending your mana on healing the pet.  A good example of not nuking with no healer is when duo'd with a Wizard.  Let them do the nuking, you handle the heals and tanking.  Actual field testing is my last piece of info I want.  I'll report back on this soon. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=523387"> Baron Drannor Soulslinger, 57 Conjurer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
